Subject: New Bridge patch for 2.3.x - Give this a whirl to test it.
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/1/9/104

Hi There!
The bridge code between late 2.0.x and 2.3.x (apart from the current 
2.2.14 updates) has hardly changed apart from some structure renaming. 
 Here is the comapnion patch to the one that went into 2.2.14.
IMPORTANT: Go to 
http://lrp.plain.co.nz/tarballs
 to download the new 
brcfg (in bridgex_0.30.tar.gz) that you will NEED.
Cheers,
Matthew Grant
